(Work In Progress)

Example setup with two nodes

1. Set up Redis to listen on localhost on the default port
   
   http://redis.io

2. Start node 1: 

mvn -Dvtk.extensions=akka-redis-cluster -Dvtk.cluster.port=6263 -Dakka.cluster.seed-nodes.0=akka.tcp://ClusterSystem@127.0.0.1:6262 -Dakka.cluster.seed-nodes.1=akka.tcp://ClusterSystem@127.0.0.1:6263 -Dvtk.listen=localhost:9321,localhost:9322 -Dvtk.webdav.port=9321 -Dvtk.web.port=9322 spring-boot:run

(Web access on http://localhost:9322, WebDAV access on http://localhost:9321)

3. Start node 2:

mvn -Dvtk.extensions=akka-redis-cluster -Dvtk.cluster.port=6262 -Dakka.cluster.seed-nodes.0=akka.tcp://ClusterSystem@127.0.0.1:6262 -Dakka.cluster.seed-nodes.1=akka.tcp://ClusterSystem@127.0.0.1:6263 -Dvtk.listen=localhost:9323,localhost:9324 -Dvtk.webdav.port=9323 -Dvtk.web.port=9324 spring-boot:run

(Web access on http://localhost:9324, WebDAV access on http://localhost:9323)
